@startuml
title Deadlock Prevention Logic

start

:Source requests permission\nto deploy a new part;

if (Process 1 free?) then (yes)
else (no)
    :Do not deploy;
    :Wait and retry;
    stop
endif

if (Process 2 waiting\nfor Process 1?) then (yes)
    :Prioritize Product B\nfrom Process 2;
    :Do not deploy Product A;
    stop
else (no)
endif

if (Crane idle?) then (yes)
else (no)
    :Wait until crane is available;
    stop
endif

if (Part already waiting\nfor pickup?) then (yes)
    :Do not create another part;
    stop
else (no)
endif

:Deploy product;

:Part requests transport;

if (Crane accepts request?) then (yes)
    :Reserve crane;
    :Pick product;
    :Transport product;
    :Release reservation;
else (no)
    :Retry negotiation later;
endif

stop

note right
Deadlock prevention mechanisms:

- Process reservation removed
- Source deployment gated
- Crane busy-state checks
- Retry instead of blocking
- Product B priority when
  Process 2 must release into Process 1
end note

@enduml